=====================Git======================

Git: status, add, commit, log, branch, switch, merge, pull, push, stash

Repository
git init

→ Start Git in current folder.

git clone URL

→ Download an existing repository.

git status

→ Show current state of files.

Adding Files
git add file.py

→ Stage one file for commit.

git add .

→ Stage all changed files.

git restore --staged file.py

→ Remove file from staging area.

Commits
git commit -m "message"

→ Save staged changes.

git commit --amend

→ Edit last commit.

git log

→ View commit history.

git log --oneline

→ Compact history view.

Differences
git diff

→ Show unstaged changes.

git diff --staged

→ Show staged changes.

Branches
git branch

→ List branches.

git branch new-feature

→ Create branch.

git switch new-feature

→ Move to branch.

git switch -c new-feature

→ Create and switch.

git merge new-feature

→ Merge branch into current.

git branch -d new-feature

→ Delete branch.

Undoing Stuff
git restore file.py

→ Discard local changes.

git reset --soft HEAD~1

→ Remove last commit, keep changes.

git reset --hard HEAD~1

→ Delete last commit and changes.

Stash
git stash

→ Temporarily save work.

git stash list

→ Show stashes.

git stash pop

→ Restore latest stash.

Remote Repositories
git remote -v

→ Show connected remotes.

git remote add origin URL

→ Connect GitHub repo.

git fetch

→ Download updates only.

git pull

→ Fetch + merge updates.

git push

→ Upload commits.

git push -u origin main

→ First push and track branch.

Rebase
git rebase main

→ Replay commits on top of main.

git pull --rebase

→ Pull without merge commit.

Tags
git tag v1.0

→ Create version tag.

git push origin v1.0

→ Upload tag.

GitHub CLI (optional)

Install:

gh auth login

→ Login to GitHub.

gh repo create

→ Create repo from terminal.

gh repo clone user/repo

→ Clone repo.

gh pr create

→ Create Pull Request.

gh pr list

→ View Pull Requests.
